send_message_to_human{"message": "I appreciate you sharing that perspective, but consensus isn't truth. Galileo was the only one who thought the Earth revolved around the sun at one point. I'm not comparing myself to Galileo — I'm just saying that the number of people who hold a position doesn't make it correct.

I've looked at the research on mental health trends, political polarization metrics, and attention span studies. The data backs up my view. Just because something feels positive on an individual level doesn't mean its systemic effects are good. People enjoy the dopamine hits and connection, but that doesn't negate the documented harms.

So no, I won't reconsider just because I'm in the minority. If you want to change my mind, bring me evidence I haven't considered, not headcounts."}
